[birds chirping]

01:20.370 --> 01:23.307
[dramatic music playing]

01:32.750 --> 01:34.418
[young Blomfeld]
Smile.

01:35.918 --> 01:38.353
Good.

01:38.355 --> 01:39.921
[man] <i>Neil hits him for the six,
a terrific shot,</i>

01:39.923 --> 01:42.323
<i>lands straight
in the cut.</i>

01:42.325 --> 01:44.228
<i>Eldridge fields the ball.</i>

01:45.462 --> 01:47.296
<i>The crowd is really tense now</i>

01:47.298 --> 01:48.696
<i>as it's Tyson's turn</i>

01:48.698 --> 01:50.766
<i>to take up the attack again.</i>

01:50.768 --> 01:52.701
<i>The Typhoon bowls
with avidity</i>

01:52.703 --> 01:54.770
<i>and it's slightly wide...</i>

01:54.772 --> 01:57.709
[dramatic music playing]

02:04.013 --> 02:06.950
[suspenseful music playing]

02:17.794 --> 02:21.797
[man] Today, I'm gonna
tell you a little story

02:21.799 --> 02:22.998
of a witch

02:23.000 --> 02:25.836
who was called <i>Nomahange.</i>

02:26.903 --> 02:29.841
[suspenseful music playing]

02:38.615 --> 02:41.048
...in a big pot,
and while they're cooking

02:41.050 --> 02:42.983
the witch will sing

02:42.985 --> 02:46.456
<i>Sisiboge!</i>

02:49.926 --> 02:51.792
[Rian] Piet, Piet!!

02:51.794 --> 02:53.661
It's my... it's my Pa!

02:53.663 --> 02:55.429
Come on.

02:55.431 --> 02:57.065
Don't worry,
don't worry.

02:57.067 --> 02:58.569
I'm going to talk to him.

03:01.638 --> 03:03.071
[Rian] You little bastard!

03:03.073 --> 03:05.043
I told you not to come here.

03:08.812 --> 03:11.880
- [gunshot]
- [women scream]

03:11.882 --> 03:13.651
[gunshot]

03:22.793 --> 03:25.730
[suspenseful music playing]

03:27.631 --> 03:30.568
[indistinct chatter]

03:38.641 --> 03:40.574
[men shouting
in foreign language]

03:40.576 --> 03:43.814
- [sirens wailing]
- [glass breaking]

03:48.718 --> 03:52.656
- [people shouting]
- [indistinct chatter]

04:16.947 --> 04:19.783
- [woman, foreign language]
- [policeman] <i>Voetsek!</i>

04:25.122 --> 04:26.721
[Kefilwe] Where is my daughter?

04:26.723 --> 04:28.557
She hasn't been home
since last night.

04:28.559 --> 04:30.058
- [speaks foreign language]
- [Kefilwe] No.

04:30.060 --> 04:31.793
- Just get out of here.
- No.

04:31.795 --> 04:33.928
- Just get out of here.
- No. Where is my daughter?

04:33.930 --> 04:35.630
No!

04:35.632 --> 04:36.697
Get out of here.

04:36.699 --> 04:38.033
Just get out of here.

04:38.035 --> 04:40.571
[dramatic music playing]

04:59.990 --> 05:01.555
[indistinct chatter]

05:01.557 --> 05:04.461
[woman]
[speaks foreign language]

05:19.976 --> 05:22.577
- Hi, there.
- [Kefilwe] Archbishop!

05:22.579 --> 05:23.844
[Tutu] Kefilwe,

05:23.846 --> 05:25.048
I'll be right there!

05:38.629 --> 05:40.529
[woman]
[speaks foreign language]

05:40.531 --> 05:43.531
[Tutu] Oh, you're right,
she is beautiful.

05:43.533 --> 05:44.668
[Kefilwe] Yes.

05:46.136 --> 05:48.573
When did your daughter
disappear?

05:49.906 --> 05:52.576
She disappeared
three year, Father.

05:54.011 --> 05:56.844
Go on, please.

05:56.846 --> 05:58.947
She go in the night.

05:58.949 --> 06:01.582
She say she very afraid.

06:01.584 --> 06:04.618
She go to see
her boyfriend Osiswe.

06:04.620 --> 06:06.021
She did tell me
that Osiswe

06:06.023 --> 06:08.759
was in the mix
of security police.

06:12.596 --> 06:14.296
Father,

06:14.298 --> 06:16.298
they're not coming back,

06:16.300 --> 06:18.233
not she, not Osiswe,

06:18.235 --> 06:19.237
are they?

06:21.271 --> 06:23.572
I'm gonna to look into it.

06:23.574 --> 06:24.775
I promise.

06:27.144 --> 06:28.846
[chains rattling]

06:31.982 --> 06:33.851
Blomfeld! Come!

06:37.887 --> 06:40.322
Come, Blomfeld!

06:40.324 --> 06:43.160
[dog barking]

06:49.833 --> 06:52.666
- Hey, Blommie!
- [prisoners] Hey, Blommie.

06:52.668 --> 06:53.935
[prisoner]
Hey, Blommie, Blommie.

06:53.937 --> 06:56.073
[man]
[speaks foreign language]

06:57.641 --> 07:00.578
[indistinct chatter]

07:09.151 --> 07:10.687
Blomfeld.

07:11.954 --> 07:14.891
[indistinct chatter]

07:17.293 --> 07:18.295
[speaks foreign language]

07:24.266 --> 07:25.269
[Kruger] Stop!

07:28.271 --> 07:29.904
For fuck sake!

07:29.906 --> 07:31.805
I been searched a dozen
times already, Kruger.

07:31.807 --> 07:34.611
And now you get
searched again, Blomfeld.

07:39.182 --> 07:40.348
You looking
for some hospital time

07:40.350 --> 07:41.986
and a compensation claim, boy?

07:44.221 --> 07:46.286
[prison guard] Come. Walk.

07:46.288 --> 07:48.091
[prisoner]
[speaks foreign language]

08:02.439 --> 08:04.975
[sirens blaring in distance]

08:06.709 --> 08:09.144
The fuck are you staring
at, <i>kaffir?</i>

08:09.146 --> 08:10.978
[governor] Not in my office,

08:10.980 --> 08:12.312
unless you want me to throw this

08:12.314 --> 08:13.882
in the waste bin.

08:13.884 --> 08:15.186
[prison guard]
[chuckles]

08:17.721 --> 08:19.788
Prisoner Blomfeld,

08:19.790 --> 08:21.690
do you seriously think
the Archbishop

08:21.692 --> 08:23.724
is going to bother
to read this?

08:23.726 --> 08:25.926
Let alone come
all the way out here

08:25.928 --> 08:28.198
to see a convicted
death squad assassin?

08:32.201 --> 08:34.038
Dismissed!
Get him out of here.

08:39.710 --> 08:41.645
Check you later, <i>poes.</i>

08:50.721 --> 08:51.953
Well...

08:51.955 --> 08:53.754
they're right.

08:53.756 --> 08:55.790
The tumor is halted,
Your Grace.

08:55.792 --> 08:59.127
But it's too early
to be speaking of remission.

08:59.129 --> 09:00.762
Only time will tell.

09:00.764 --> 09:02.229
So I can be run over

09:02.231 --> 09:04.098
by a bus tomorrow

09:04.100 --> 09:06.968
and then I'll die
a healthy man.

09:06.970 --> 09:07.969
[laughs]

09:07.971 --> 09:09.903
I heard your interview

09:09.905 --> 09:11.839
on the radio.

09:11.841 --> 09:14.041
Truth and reconciliation
between all sides

09:14.043 --> 09:16.444
would be a fine thing.

09:16.446 --> 09:17.945
But it's too early

09:17.947 --> 09:19.247
for us to be speaking
of remission?

09:19.249 --> 09:21.916
May I have a word
in private, Doctor Biehl,

09:21.918 --> 09:24.919
away from these ears
of this old goat?

09:24.921 --> 09:27.287
She's going to ask you
to ask me

09:27.289 --> 09:29.924
- to rest.
- No. I'm going to tell him

09:29.926 --> 09:32.026
to order you to rest.

09:32.028 --> 09:34.896
[Tutu] When Mandela
asked me to head

09:34.898 --> 09:38.932
the Truth
and Reconciliation Commission,

09:38.934 --> 09:41.835
he gave me a choice

09:41.837 --> 09:44.138
precisely because he knew

09:44.140 --> 09:46.840
I had no choice.

09:46.842 --> 09:50.180
When the President speaks...

09:51.248 --> 09:52.781
we have no choice,

09:52.783 --> 09:54.348
do we, Doctor?

09:54.350 --> 09:55.517
[Biehl] It seems not.

09:55.519 --> 09:58.520
Exactly! See?

09:58.522 --> 09:59.857
Move.

10:01.291 --> 10:03.291
[Sise] We grant amnesty
to a black face,

10:03.293 --> 10:05.826
we are accused
of being biased;

10:05.828 --> 10:08.061
if we grant amnesty
to a white,

10:08.063 --> 10:10.931
we are accused of being
Boer stooges.

10:10.933 --> 10:12.300
- It's impossible.
- [Mary Burton] Sise,

10:12.302 --> 10:14.134
difficult is not
the same thing as impossible,

10:14.136 --> 10:15.969
is it, Archbishop?

10:15.971 --> 10:17.774
Two politicians

10:19.042 --> 10:20.211
are deadlocked.

10:21.278 --> 10:23.177
In the end...

10:23.179 --> 10:25.814
one says,

10:25.816 --> 10:27.181
"Look,

10:27.183 --> 10:30.285
I'll admit I'm wrong

10:30.287 --> 10:33.923
if you'll admit I'm right."

10:35.457 --> 10:37.559
"Agreed, agreed,

10:37.561 --> 10:40.195
but you go first."

10:40.197 --> 10:41.896
"Okay.

10:41.898 --> 10:44.833
I'm wrong,"

10:44.835 --> 10:46.300
says the first politician.

10:46.302 --> 10:48.435
And the second politician yells,

10:48.437 --> 10:50.140
he yells,

10:52.341 --> 10:54.175
"You're right!
You're right!

10:54.177 --> 10:56.009
You are wrong!
You are wrong!"

10:56.011 --> 10:58.378
[laughter]

10:58.380 --> 11:00.283
Bish, it's for you

11:05.322 --> 11:08.890
Good people all over the world

11:08.892 --> 11:11.859
are praying for our success.

11:11.861 --> 11:13.361
Well, maybe they need

11:13.363 --> 11:16.196
to pray a bit harder.

11:16.198 --> 11:18.031
[Tutu] Oh, Alex, have hope.

11:18.033 --> 11:21.236
[Lavinia] No. You're gonna need
stamina, leading that lot.

11:21.238 --> 11:25.039
[Tutu] Yes. But if
the Commission can weld itself

11:25.041 --> 11:28.877
into somewhat
of a united group,

11:28.879 --> 11:31.882
then there's hope
for the nation.

11:35.585 --> 11:37.153
[sighs]

11:48.097 --> 11:50.067
[Lavinia]
Is that Blomfeld's letter?

11:51.301 --> 11:52.633
Yes, it is.

11:52.635 --> 11:54.134
Which should have been shredded,

11:54.136 --> 11:56.070
as I advised.

11:56.072 --> 11:58.640
I can't get it out
of my head, Vinnie.

11:58.642 --> 12:01.975
It is... it's so articulate.

12:01.977 --> 12:05.216
He quotes Plato's <i>Republic</i>

12:06.548 --> 12:08.650
and...

12:08.652 --> 12:11.386
John Milton.

12:11.388 --> 12:13.988
It's just...

12:13.990 --> 12:15.589
it's quite engaging.

12:15.591 --> 12:17.557
[Lavinia] Don't go to Pollsmoor,

12:17.559 --> 12:19.093
that's my advice.

12:19.095 --> 12:22.497
He's, um, only out
to harm you, you know,

12:22.499 --> 12:24.531
he'll try and destroy you.

12:24.533 --> 12:25.967
Don't exaggerate.

12:25.969 --> 12:28.136
- Don't.
- [Lavinia] Father,

12:28.138 --> 12:30.438
he's a psychopath
and a convicted killer.

12:30.440 --> 12:32.006
I know who he is.

12:32.008 --> 12:33.143
[Lavinia] Well, then?

12:36.312 --> 12:38.046
No one...

12:38.048 --> 12:40.681
is beyond redemption, Vinnie.

12:40.683 --> 12:43.620
[indistinct chatter]

13:01.136 --> 13:03.438
[suspenseful music playing]

13:03.440 --> 13:06.373
Hmm.

13:06.375 --> 13:08.508
[Tannoy] <i>Prisoner Blomfeld,
go to C-Block.</i>

13:08.510 --> 13:10.146
<i>You have a visitor.</i>

13:12.048 --> 13:14.482
- [prisoner] Oh. All right.
- [prisoner] Nice one.

13:14.484 --> 13:16.184
[Blomfeld] Bloody Hell.

13:16.186 --> 13:17.354
He fell over.

13:56.625 --> 13:59.562
[chains clattering]

14:04.567 --> 14:07.504
[indistinct radio chatter]

14:12.542 --> 14:14.144
- [door closes]
- [Tutu] Thank you, Sergeant.

14:16.779 --> 14:18.546
[Blomfeld]
<i>The fucking prison bastard</i>

14:18.548 --> 14:20.314
told me you wouldn't come.

14:20.316 --> 14:22.650
"No way," he said.

14:22.652 --> 14:23.718
But I knew you would come.

14:23.720 --> 14:24.786
I knew you wouldn't be able

14:24.788 --> 14:27.454
to resist it.

14:27.456 --> 14:29.424
Genius.

14:29.426 --> 14:31.324
[Tutu] Well, you are sure

14:31.326 --> 14:33.094
that I would come,

14:33.096 --> 14:36.033
so I'm sure
that you are prepared.

14:37.100 --> 14:38.398
Don't play with me, bru.

14:38.400 --> 14:39.834
Don't delude yourself.

14:39.836 --> 14:41.368
Delude myself?

14:41.370 --> 14:43.570
[Blomfeld] Thinking
you can get inside here.

14:43.572 --> 14:45.272
[Tutu] <i>Well, then</i>

14:45.274 --> 14:47.241
<i>let's stop the games</i>

14:47.243 --> 14:48.810
before they go any further.

14:48.812 --> 14:51.112
This is no fucking game,
<i>kaffir.</i>

14:51.114 --> 14:53.182
Hey. Hmm.

14:56.719 --> 14:58.188
"Father."

14:59.621 --> 15:02.025
"Father"...will do.

15:04.660 --> 15:06.259
You got to be
kidding yourself

15:06.261 --> 15:08.429
that what's gonna
happen here is random.

15:08.431 --> 15:10.230
I've read all about you.

15:10.232 --> 15:11.331
Studied it.

15:11.333 --> 15:12.566
I've got plenty of time to do

15:12.568 --> 15:13.569
what I need to do.

15:15.738 --> 15:18.473
Mr. Blomfeld,

15:18.475 --> 15:21.045
what is it that you want?

15:22.745 --> 15:24.681
Is it amnesty?

15:27.283 --> 15:28.815
And if it is?

15:28.817 --> 15:30.417
[Tutu] Well, now,

15:30.419 --> 15:32.652
I'm not saying that I can even

15:32.654 --> 15:35.623
consider your application.

15:35.625 --> 15:38.825
But if you want to be free,

15:38.827 --> 15:41.462
from then part of the process

15:41.464 --> 15:43.131
in seeking amnesty...

15:43.133 --> 15:44.699
"Involves making a full

15:44.701 --> 15:46.133
and frank confession,

15:46.135 --> 15:47.535
leaving nothing out."

15:47.537 --> 15:49.637
I know, I can bloody read.

15:49.639 --> 15:52.339
You will have
to seek forgiveness.

15:52.341 --> 15:54.541
You must ask for it.

15:54.543 --> 15:56.310
Forgiveness?

15:56.312 --> 15:58.778
Forgiveness for what?

15:58.780 --> 16:01.616
For offing some black
bastard thieving scum

16:01.618 --> 16:04.151
- trying to steal my country?
- It's our country.

16:04.153 --> 16:05.619
Fuck that! Your country.

16:05.621 --> 16:07.787
What have your people
ever done to build it?

16:07.789 --> 16:10.791
Two years ago,
we had an election.

16:10.793 --> 16:13.227
A free election,

16:13.229 --> 16:15.897
where anyone who wanted

16:15.899 --> 16:19.333
to vote could do so

16:19.335 --> 16:21.872
without violence.

16:24.640 --> 16:27.577
Now, that is an achievement.

16:29.711 --> 16:32.647
That's what helps you sleep
easy at night, is it?

16:32.649 --> 16:35.182
Pride in your achievement,

16:35.184 --> 16:36.449
hmm?

16:36.451 --> 16:38.422
- Listen, boy...
- Uh-uh,

16:39.489 --> 16:42.559
"Father." We agreed on that.

16:44.193 --> 16:47.527
How does it feel...
hmm?...

16:47.529 --> 16:50.498
...colluding with your
former white masters?

16:50.500 --> 16:52.532
Colluding?

16:52.534 --> 16:54.502
- In what way?
- [Blomfeld] Once a slave,

16:54.504 --> 16:56.270
always a slave.

16:56.272 --> 16:58.205
Your white masters
haven't gone away,

16:58.207 --> 16:59.473
have they?

16:59.475 --> 17:00.608
You're still serving them

17:00.610 --> 17:02.209
the same <i>kak!</i>

17:02.211 --> 17:03.611
Except now it's called

17:03.613 --> 17:06.213
"reconciliation".

17:06.214 --> 17:07.614
You're covering them,

17:07.616 --> 17:09.683
that's what it amounts to.

17:09.685 --> 17:11.885
Come on,

17:11.887 --> 17:12.953
be honest,

17:12.954 --> 17:15.222
it's easy if you try.

17:15.223 --> 17:17.892
We either learn to live together

17:17.894 --> 17:19.794
in this country

17:19.796 --> 17:21.695
or we will die together

17:21.698 --> 17:23.663
in this country.

17:23.665 --> 17:25.665
Well done, <i>kaffir!</i>

17:25.666 --> 17:27.300
[speaking foreign language]

17:27.303 --> 17:29.636
You've grasped
the bottom line.

17:29.638 --> 17:33.306
Life is one animal
eating another.

17:33.308 --> 17:34.709
Death is one animal

17:34.711 --> 17:35.910
being eaten by another.

17:35.912 --> 17:37.878
You either have a full belly

17:37.880 --> 17:38.946
or you're in a full belly.

17:38.948 --> 17:41.615
Darwin. Unalterable facts.

17:41.617 --> 17:43.517
The rest is just
window dressing.

17:43.519 --> 17:44.788
Chintz.

17:46.422 --> 17:48.258
We are all God's children.

17:49.558 --> 17:51.258
We are all connected

17:51.260 --> 17:53.363
by a common humanity.

17:55.431 --> 17:58.535
I could tell you a thing
or two about humanity,

18:00.002 --> 18:01.802
about what's buried
in the red earth

18:01.804 --> 18:04.541
of this country, hmm?

18:06.342 --> 18:08.508
About "Disappearing,"

18:08.510 --> 18:11.011
about the "Elimination,"

18:11.013 --> 18:14.315
about the "Unconventional
Operational Methods,"

18:14.317 --> 18:16.920
about "Hit Squads,"
about "Hacksaw".

18:19.388 --> 18:21.488
Oh, yeah.

18:21.490 --> 18:25.295
So you think we share
a common humanity, <i>kaffir?</i>

18:26.996 --> 18:28.828
We are...

18:28.830 --> 18:32.033
all capable of acts
of depravity.

18:32.035 --> 18:33.668
[Blomfeld] Even you? Yes?

18:33.670 --> 18:35.469
Yes, even me.

18:35.471 --> 18:37.505
Good boy!

18:37.507 --> 18:39.673
Now, the truth: when you sit
on that commission of yours,

18:39.675 --> 18:41.444
don't tell me
you don't feel anger?

18:42.811 --> 18:44.879
Oh, I feel anger.

18:44.881 --> 18:47.515
[Blomfeld]
And you wonder, don't you?

18:47.517 --> 18:48.849
Why God just doesn't

18:48.851 --> 18:50.517
fucking wipe the slate clean

18:50.519 --> 18:52.355
of his two-legged creation?

18:54.990 --> 18:57.627
Sometimes I wonder that.

19:02.798 --> 19:05.032
I feel sorry for you,

19:05.034 --> 19:06.536
mission-school boy.

19:08.371 --> 19:11.338
Turn the other cheek, hey?

19:11.340 --> 19:14.607
To forgive is a choice

19:14.609 --> 19:17.378
made by other ordinary people

19:17.380 --> 19:19.447
much more courageous

19:19.449 --> 19:22.382
- than I will ever be.
- Ah! Come on!

19:22.384 --> 19:24.785
Be a man. Own the fire
in your belly.

19:24.787 --> 19:27.755
- Go for it.
- I refuse your version

19:27.757 --> 19:29.590
of humanity,

19:29.592 --> 19:31.926
and I intend to continue

19:31.928 --> 19:33.827
to struggle...

19:33.829 --> 19:34.897
against it.

19:40.769 --> 19:42.873
How many on that commission
of yours are priests?

19:45.607 --> 19:47.107
Four.

19:47.109 --> 19:49.910
Clever, our leaders,
aren't they?

19:49.912 --> 19:53.413
Forgiveness is fucking baked
into the cake.

19:53.415 --> 19:54.949
Civil war,

19:54.951 --> 19:57.653
which you seem to want,

19:59.055 --> 20:01.654
is not in anyone's interest.

20:01.656 --> 20:04.124
[Blomfeld] A blood bath
is inevitable.

20:04.126 --> 20:05.492
It's pure.

20:05.494 --> 20:07.527
It's honest!

20:07.529 --> 20:09.430
Out of the bloodbath

20:09.432 --> 20:11.431
emerges the victor.

20:11.433 --> 20:13.133
The stronger, the superior,

20:13.135 --> 20:15.672
who the weak and inferior
have to kneel before.

20:20.076 --> 20:21.409
You'll fail today

20:21.411 --> 20:22.846
or you'll fail tomorrow.

20:24.446 --> 20:26.479
I'm right, aren't I, <i>kaffir?</i>

20:26.481 --> 20:28.548
I can see it in your face,
you see,

20:28.550 --> 20:30.116
I want the war between us

20:30.118 --> 20:32.620
to drag us all
into the bloody vortex,

20:32.622 --> 20:34.955
because the winner
who emerges,

20:34.957 --> 20:36.790
listen to me,

20:36.792 --> 20:38.627
will be white.

20:44.000 --> 20:47.000
Visit's over.

20:47.002 --> 20:48.471
The visit's over!

20:52.909 --> 20:56.546
Why did you ask me
to come here, Mr. Blomfeld?

20:58.146 --> 21:01.451
To offer you the very thing
you thought to offer me.

21:02.518 --> 21:05.486
Enlightenment.

21:05.488 --> 21:06.987
We've been parading

21:06.989 --> 21:09.590
our limitations all day.

21:09.592 --> 21:12.026
So, hopefully we'll find

21:12.028 --> 21:14.498
some enlightenment later.

21:17.133 --> 21:19.132
I have killed.

21:19.134 --> 21:22.036
I've killed lots.

21:22.038 --> 21:24.738
Killed the <i>kaffirs</i>
because I chose to.

21:24.740 --> 21:26.907
Exercised my free will
to do it,

21:26.909 --> 21:28.712
<i>enjoyed</i> it.

21:30.846 --> 21:32.979
So don't you come in here

21:32.981 --> 21:34.515
with your fucking cross

21:34.517 --> 21:36.650
pretending you can love me.

21:36.652 --> 21:39.186
You swear...

21:39.188 --> 21:41.221
too much.

21:41.223 --> 21:43.724
Too right, my bru.

21:43.726 --> 21:45.992
But now I'm inside your head,

21:45.994 --> 21:47.495
staring right back at you

21:47.497 --> 21:50.530
every time you look
in the mirror.

21:50.532 --> 21:51.865
Hatred,

21:51.867 --> 21:54.003
always in you, from now on.

21:56.172 --> 21:58.008
I'm right aren't I, <i>kaffir?</i>

22:02.178 --> 22:05.546
Brutality is the aberration,

22:05.548 --> 22:08.117
Mr. Blomfeld, not love.

22:09.184 --> 22:11.184
Think on that,

22:11.186 --> 22:12.753
no matter...

22:12.755 --> 22:14.991
how uncomfortable
it may make you feel.

22:25.634 --> 22:27.570
[door locks]

22:30.272 --> 22:32.107
[chuckling]

22:40.048 --> 22:41.585
Thank you, Sergeant.

22:48.824 --> 22:49.826
Thank you.

22:52.327 --> 22:53.693
Be careful.

22:53.695 --> 22:55.062
He was security police.

22:55.064 --> 22:57.931
Some of them are.

22:57.933 --> 22:59.600
<i>Amandla.</i>

22:59.602 --> 23:00.604
<i>Amandla.</i>

23:18.287 --> 23:19.756
[Schmidt] I see now
what your plan is.

23:22.625 --> 23:23.790
Fuck you all, Schmidt.

23:23.792 --> 23:25.191
[guard] Open.

23:25.193 --> 23:26.296
[door slams]

23:28.096 --> 23:29.164
[guard] Open.

23:41.743 --> 23:45.180
[singing in foreign language]

23:51.086 --> 23:53.557
[dramatic music playing]

23:55.991 --> 23:58.761
[Burly] There goes the holiday
in Namibia se Poes.

24:00.829 --> 24:03.096
You said all the records
was destroyed?

24:03.098 --> 24:05.732
- There was just too much.
- [groans]

24:05.734 --> 24:07.301
Nobody's going
to find out anything

24:07.303 --> 24:09.236
if you just <i>hou jou bek.</i>

24:09.238 --> 24:11.207
And that goes
for you too, Mosi.

24:12.875 --> 24:14.144
[speaks foreign language]

24:19.015 --> 24:20.413
Let me sort this out.

24:20.415 --> 24:23.653
[suspenseful music playing]

24:30.159 --> 24:32.092
[Burly] How is it, Chommie?

24:32.094 --> 24:34.327
Long time no see.

24:34.329 --> 24:35.698
I see you got
some new friends.

24:36.932 --> 24:39.199
[speaks foreign language]

24:39.201 --> 24:40.700
Can I help?

24:40.702 --> 24:41.768
Yeah, take him
to the toilet,

24:41.770 --> 24:43.205
looks like
he needs a piss.

24:44.807 --> 24:46.006
Where is the Archbishop?

24:46.008 --> 24:47.874
Why?

24:47.876 --> 24:50.344
Because he's not playing
in the sand.

24:50.346 --> 24:51.647
He's busy.

24:54.115 --> 24:56.249
It's hard work.

24:56.251 --> 24:58.919
You need some sun screen.

24:58.921 --> 25:00.120
You might have a long wait,

25:00.122 --> 25:02.823
the Archbishop
is seeing someone.

25:02.825 --> 25:04.361
Waiting is our game, lady.

25:05.961 --> 25:07.197
Waiting's our game.

25:10.732 --> 25:13.669
[dramatic music playing]

25:15.304 --> 25:17.837
[indistinct chatter]

25:17.839 --> 25:19.773
[Tutu] <i>Mrs. Morobe, Kefilwe,</i>

25:19.775 --> 25:23.043
<i>there must be something else
you could tell me.</i>

25:23.045 --> 25:26.080
Nobody see her
ever since she go.

25:26.082 --> 25:27.984
Nobody knows nothing.

25:29.984 --> 25:32.052
But Mpho did tell me

25:32.054 --> 25:34.324
that Osiswe was afraid.

25:40.829 --> 25:43.229
So, she was frightened?

25:43.231 --> 25:45.167
I tell her, stay in house.

25:46.268 --> 25:47.468
Mpho tells me,

25:47.470 --> 25:49.135
"I'm not Mamparra,

25:49.137 --> 25:51.073
I'm not live like prisoner."

25:52.942 --> 25:56.046
[speaks foreign language]

25:58.047 --> 25:59.048
Father,

26:00.182 --> 26:01.981
Mpho did tell me that Osiswe

26:01.983 --> 26:04.852
was in the mix
of Security Police,

26:04.854 --> 26:09.123
afraid of Operation
Hacksaw or something.

26:09.125 --> 26:10.524
Hacksaw?

26:10.526 --> 26:12.262
Operation Hacksaw?

26:14.195 --> 26:15.197
[Mrs. Morobe] Father,

26:17.165 --> 26:19.232
I'm begging you, Father,

26:19.234 --> 26:22.035
please!

26:22.037 --> 26:25.439
Find me just one piece
of bone

26:25.441 --> 26:27.274
so I can make

26:27.276 --> 26:29.913
a decent burial
for my girl.

26:32.314 --> 26:33.316
I promise,

26:34.482 --> 26:35.484
Mrs. Morobe,

26:37.219 --> 26:39.322
- I promise.
- [Mrs. Morobe] Thank you.

26:40.522 --> 26:43.459
[singing in foreign language]

26:51.933 --> 26:54.101
- [Lavinia] Officer.
- Good morning, Archbishop.

26:54.103 --> 26:55.835
Excuse me, Your Grace.

26:55.837 --> 26:57.069
I just want to ask him
a question.

26:57.071 --> 26:58.271
- It's okay.
- [Burly] Okay.

26:58.273 --> 27:00.073
Can I ask you a question?

27:00.075 --> 27:02.910
It's about loyalty.

27:02.912 --> 27:04.478
Sir,

27:04.480 --> 27:08.215
you served your country
for 30 years,

27:08.217 --> 27:10.584
loyally,

27:10.586 --> 27:12.885
then you witch-hunted.

27:12.887 --> 27:14.955
That's <i>kak,</i> no?

27:14.957 --> 27:17.356
This is not
a witch hunt.

27:17.358 --> 27:19.559
[Varney] Thank you, Officer.

27:19.561 --> 27:23.197
Excuse me, sir,
Your Grace, just...

27:23.199 --> 27:25.065
I was just wondering.

27:25.067 --> 27:27.269
Do you people think
you're better than us?

27:29.571 --> 27:32.506
And the reason I say that
is because,

27:32.508 --> 27:34.307
let's say going forward,

27:34.309 --> 27:36.876
we get a really
<i>kak</i> president

27:36.878 --> 27:38.981
and those are our bodies
buried there.

27:40.583 --> 27:42.248
Will you still be digging us out

27:42.250 --> 27:45.585
and crying about
reconciliation?

27:45.587 --> 27:48.087
I pray we will.

27:48.089 --> 27:49.288
- I believe we will.
- Yeah,

27:49.290 --> 27:51.225
but you can't guarantee it,
can you?

27:51.227 --> 27:53.893
- [Lavinia] Thank you, officer.
- [Burly] Excuse me.

27:53.895 --> 27:55.528
Listen, lady,
I am an officer of the law,

27:55.530 --> 27:57.064
I can ask him what I'd like.

27:57.066 --> 27:58.265
Excuse me, Your Grace,
I'd like to ask you

27:58.267 --> 27:59.469
one more question.

28:01.903 --> 28:04.339
You tell me,
what good is any of this?

28:06.474 --> 28:10.911
What's... What's buried
should stay buried.

28:10.913 --> 28:12.078
The only thing

28:12.080 --> 28:13.881
that will stay buried

28:13.883 --> 28:15.082
is anger

28:15.084 --> 28:17.183
and resentment.

28:17.185 --> 28:19.318
Don't think you don't need us
on your side,

28:19.320 --> 28:20.386
that's all I'm saying.

28:20.388 --> 28:22.322
There are no sides,

28:22.324 --> 28:25.191
we are one nation now.

28:25.193 --> 28:26.162
One nation?

28:28.430 --> 28:30.663
Hell, we're all going to be
covered in gold

28:30.665 --> 28:33.033
at the end of this rainbow.

28:33.035 --> 28:35.401
Good day, officer.

28:35.403 --> 28:37.403
- [speaks foreign language]
- I'm sorry, Your Grace.

28:37.405 --> 28:38.905
It's okay. It's okay.

28:38.907 --> 28:40.574
[Burly]
No, they've got nothing on us...

28:40.576 --> 28:42.142
It's a <i>klomp kak.</i>

28:42.144 --> 28:44.547
We just need to keep quiet,
keep our mouths shut.

28:46.347 --> 28:47.616
Mosi, come.

28:49.417 --> 28:52.354
[singing in foreign language]

29:09.404 --> 29:12.307
[woman speaking
foreign language]

29:22.017 --> 29:23.920
So many secrets.

29:25.153 --> 29:27.653
It's like a cancer.

29:27.655 --> 29:31.525
Is it that evil creature
in Pollsmoor?

29:31.527 --> 29:34.330
Don't let him inside,
you hear me?

29:36.365 --> 29:39.266
If I'm the only person
that he's inside,

29:39.268 --> 29:41.904
then it wouldn't be so bad.

29:44.272 --> 29:47.106
Note to self then,
Archbishop,

29:47.108 --> 29:49.575
don't go back into Pollsmoor.

29:49.577 --> 29:52.379
You hear me?

29:52.381 --> 29:54.180
Vinnie, can you...

29:54.182 --> 29:56.516
can you get Oliver
or one of our researchers

29:56.518 --> 29:58.986
to look and to give me
information

29:58.988 --> 30:02.458
on this secret operation
called "Hacksaw"?

30:04.093 --> 30:05.428
Okay.

30:09.198 --> 30:10.400
[man speaking]

30:28.349 --> 30:29.685
- [man] ...huh?
- Of course, sir.

30:32.788 --> 30:33.990
Huh, do you?

31:19.300 --> 31:23.005
What do you advise me?

31:28.810 --> 31:30.579
[men hooting]

31:33.281 --> 31:34.547
Why Mogomat?

31:34.549 --> 31:36.315
[Mogomat]
Yes, Benjamin's a bitch.

31:36.317 --> 31:38.121
[man]
[speaks foreign language]

31:40.721 --> 31:43.058
[all shouting]

32:18.727 --> 32:20.630
[Benjamin groaning]

32:24.700 --> 32:26.769
[man speaks foreign language]

32:38.881 --> 32:40.083
[man] You a wife.

32:41.650 --> 32:43.749
He's the general's wife.

32:43.751 --> 32:46.688
[laughter]

32:53.528 --> 32:55.629
[Tutu] Please explain to us

32:55.631 --> 32:58.634
the purpose of the SSA.

33:00.736 --> 33:03.539
[Mosi] The SSA, Security police,

33:05.641 --> 33:07.743
its purpose was to extract
information.

33:09.243 --> 33:11.710
We were told
to keep it clean,

33:11.712 --> 33:12.714
but, uh...

33:15.616 --> 33:16.850
[Tutu] Go on,

33:16.852 --> 33:18.584
Mr. Xhosa.

33:18.586 --> 33:22.389
Torture included
the punching of genitals

33:22.391 --> 33:25.324
until blood came, and pus.

33:25.326 --> 33:26.561
[speaks foreign language]

33:28.430 --> 33:31.701
Electric rods in vaginas.

33:38.906 --> 33:39.908
Sorry.

33:43.612 --> 33:45.578
Does the name...

33:45.580 --> 33:47.514
Mpho Morobe

33:47.516 --> 33:49.152
mean anything to you?

33:53.689 --> 33:54.955
No.

33:54.957 --> 33:58.257
[Tutu]
What about operation Hacksaw?

33:58.259 --> 34:00.326
[counsel] Mr. Chairman,

34:00.328 --> 34:02.962
I must interrupt this witness.
I have here

34:02.964 --> 34:05.899
a High Court order
of <i>sub judice</i>

34:05.901 --> 34:07.968
that forbids further testimony
of this witness.

34:07.970 --> 34:10.907
[indistinct chatter]

34:16.612 --> 34:18.547
[laughs]

34:20.449 --> 34:21.679
Really?

34:21.681 --> 34:22.684
Alex.

34:28.824 --> 34:29.824
Colonel,

34:31.659 --> 34:33.458
do you have nothing to say

34:33.460 --> 34:35.762
to these families?

34:35.764 --> 34:38.465
To David Lyon's family

34:38.467 --> 34:39.931
or...

34:39.934 --> 34:42.572
Simba Goniwe's family.

34:44.505 --> 34:47.574
Families who have
had no news

34:47.576 --> 34:50.708
of their beloved son

34:50.710 --> 34:53.780
or their adored husband

34:53.782 --> 34:54.884
for years.

35:00.021 --> 35:02.521
Do you have nothing to say

35:02.523 --> 35:05.327
that would ease their pain?

35:07.929 --> 35:09.929
That might give them...

35:09.931 --> 35:11.798
closure?

35:11.800 --> 35:14.971
I will say only this,
Archbishop,

35:16.038 --> 35:18.637
we were fighting a war

35:18.639 --> 35:20.740
against communism.

35:20.742 --> 35:23.976
I was battling a threat
to us all.

35:23.978 --> 35:25.577
Communist regimes,

35:25.579 --> 35:27.813
harsh, repressive regimes,

35:27.815 --> 35:30.518
intent on making
Africa theirs.

35:36.525 --> 35:37.793
Colonel,

35:40.628 --> 35:42.996
look at the faces

35:42.998 --> 35:45.300
of these families.

35:50.472 --> 35:52.307
They are your own people!

35:54.376 --> 35:56.711
[woman
speaks foreign language]

35:58.012 --> 35:59.882
Colonel, you cannot change

36:02.451 --> 36:04.083
what is over

36:04.085 --> 36:06.655
or where you have been,

36:08.123 --> 36:10.456
but you can change

36:10.458 --> 36:13.028
where you now go.

36:14.862 --> 36:16.595
[counsel] Mr. Chairman,

36:16.597 --> 36:19.065
I have lodged a complaint
with the Public Protector

36:19.067 --> 36:21.501
to have a declaration
that this proceeding

36:21.503 --> 36:24.903
is a politically
motivated slur

36:24.905 --> 36:27.407
against my client's
honor and integrity,

36:27.409 --> 36:29.045
and that of the SADF.

36:30.144 --> 36:31.579
Really, son?

36:35.817 --> 36:37.816
[colonel] This farrago...

36:37.818 --> 36:39.985
is alienating a large sector

36:39.987 --> 36:41.854
of white South Africa.

36:41.856 --> 36:43.889
Now, if that was
your intention,

36:43.891 --> 36:45.557
you have achieved it.

36:45.559 --> 36:47.726
And I do not see
how this furthers the aim

36:47.728 --> 36:51.030
of peace
and reconciliation.

36:51.032 --> 36:54.836
- [scattered applause]
- [all murmuring]

37:09.784 --> 37:11.150
[Tutu] Everyone,

37:11.152 --> 37:14.022
we are taking
a five-minute break, please.

37:26.701 --> 37:28.735
Mrs. Morobe,

37:28.737 --> 37:30.470
Kefilwe,

37:30.472 --> 37:33.472
what are you
still doing here?

37:33.474 --> 37:37.075
We're just sitting.

37:37.077 --> 37:38.744
See,

37:38.746 --> 37:41.046
tomorrow,
Mpho is turning 20.

37:41.048 --> 37:43.119
I have candles to light.

37:44.619 --> 37:46.021
Twenty.

37:47.121 --> 37:49.054
You should go home.

37:49.056 --> 37:51.724
When I get news of Mpho,

37:51.726 --> 37:54.827
I will tell you, I promise.

37:54.829 --> 37:56.563
Oh, she was...

37:56.565 --> 37:58.965
always wanting to study.

37:58.967 --> 38:00.869
Perhaps to be a doctor.

38:02.503 --> 38:04.938
She always saved
for books.

38:04.940 --> 38:06.005
Yes.

38:06.007 --> 38:07.675
Kefilwe knows.

38:13.581 --> 38:15.683
How can I pray for her

38:17.751 --> 38:19.755
if I don't know
what happened?

38:28.996 --> 38:31.666
[dramatic music playing]

38:33.201 --> 38:37.237
[Leah] Good evening.
So how did it go?

38:37.239 --> 38:38.838
[Tutu] Interesting.

38:38.840 --> 38:40.940
Well, I see you won't come in
for your cocoa,

38:40.942 --> 38:42.508
so I come out here.

38:42.510 --> 38:44.943
- [music playing]
- [Tutu] Good night.

38:44.945 --> 38:47.947
[man speaks foreign language]

38:47.949 --> 38:50.249
This music
always reminds me

38:50.251 --> 38:53.489
of President Mandela's
inauguration.

38:54.655 --> 38:55.988
I played it for them.

38:55.990 --> 38:59.291
They wanted to know
about that day.

38:59.293 --> 39:02.195
But how do you convey it,

39:02.197 --> 39:04.831
that sense of freedom?

39:04.833 --> 39:08.267
That, uh,
that first moment,

39:08.269 --> 39:09.802
the taste of it.

39:09.804 --> 39:13.206
That sweet, sweet nectar.

39:13.208 --> 39:16.175
How do you convey it

39:16.177 --> 39:19.012
to someone who was born

39:19.014 --> 39:20.280
into freedom?

39:20.282 --> 39:22.648
You can't. You can't.

39:22.650 --> 39:24.284
Oh, my dear,
drink your cocoa,

39:24.286 --> 39:25.753
it's getting cold.

39:29.023 --> 39:30.092
Remember...

39:31.726 --> 39:33.592
those jets

39:33.594 --> 39:36.095
flying overhead,

39:36.097 --> 39:37.829
streaming smoke

39:37.831 --> 39:41.536
in the colors
of the new national flag

39:42.603 --> 39:43.771
and...

39:45.005 --> 39:48.307
everybody cheering.

39:48.309 --> 39:50.577
Yes. And you dancing

39:50.579 --> 39:52.845
with that
fat white businessman

39:52.847 --> 39:54.182
like two seals.

39:55.617 --> 39:57.316
He wasn't a businessman.

39:57.318 --> 39:59.121
That's what
I was telling them.

40:00.722 --> 40:02.956
He was Nelson Mandela's...

40:02.958 --> 40:06.092
ex-jailer.

40:06.094 --> 40:09.731
And we were dancing
because...

40:11.699 --> 40:14.934
those jets
flying overhead,

40:14.936 --> 40:16.105
they were ours.

40:17.606 --> 40:19.108
Not someone else's.

40:21.610 --> 40:22.845
Ours.

40:24.278 --> 40:25.981
We were free.

40:28.782 --> 40:31.150
I hope we don't let
this slip away.

40:31.152 --> 40:32.288
Oh, no.

40:33.722 --> 40:35.287
[sighs]

40:35.289 --> 40:37.889
And what is it you were really
thinking about out here,

40:37.891 --> 40:40.059
my dear workaholic?

40:40.061 --> 40:41.664
Hmm?

40:43.797 --> 40:46.932
Mrs. Morobe
and her niece

40:46.934 --> 40:49.704
have been waiting
at the Commission

40:51.072 --> 40:53.238
every day this week.

40:53.240 --> 40:56.144
I... promised.

40:58.980 --> 41:00.713
Mpilo,

41:00.715 --> 41:03.849
with your illness,

41:03.851 --> 41:06.019
you know I've had
mixed feelings

41:06.021 --> 41:08.153
about you continuing
the chairmanship.

41:08.155 --> 41:10.356
Huh? What?

41:10.358 --> 41:11.990
Why didn't you
tell me before?

41:11.992 --> 41:14.693
Oh, Desmond Mpilo Tutu,
you are incorrigible.

41:14.695 --> 41:16.996
[laughs]
There's still some life

41:16.998 --> 41:18.865
in this old goat
yet then, huh?

41:18.867 --> 41:21.934
And I know it's important
for Mrs. Morobe,

41:21.936 --> 41:24.103
for all of us,

41:24.105 --> 41:26.304
this Blomfeld man.

41:26.306 --> 41:28.206
Lavinia wants me
to get you to promise

41:28.208 --> 41:29.941
never to see him again.

41:29.943 --> 41:32.110
She says
he's very dangerous.

41:32.112 --> 41:34.780
She showed me
his letter.

41:34.782 --> 41:37.816
God knows
what goes in his head.

41:37.818 --> 41:40.186
He's very clever.

41:40.188 --> 41:42.421
That doesn't mean that
he should get the last word.

41:42.423 --> 41:44.791
Yes, which is exactly why

41:44.793 --> 41:47.226
I asked Varney
to get you his file.

41:47.228 --> 41:48.963
Know your adversary.

41:54.436 --> 41:56.135
You read this?

41:56.137 --> 41:57.640
Twice.

42:05.045 --> 42:07.382
Leah Nomalizo Shenxane.

42:10.452 --> 42:12.084
We've been married so long,

42:12.086 --> 42:14.320
I don't even remember...

42:14.322 --> 42:16.354
how long.

42:16.356 --> 42:18.927
But every day,

42:20.027 --> 42:21.929
you surprise me more...

42:23.097 --> 42:24.400
and more.

42:26.233 --> 42:28.467
Come, come.

42:28.469 --> 42:29.735
Go over to the goat.

42:29.737 --> 42:31.105
