[speaks foreign language]

46:55.503 --> 46:56.735
[prisoners] Salute!

46:56.737 --> 46:58.570
[man
speaking foreign language]

46:58.572 --> 47:00.673
[Mogomat]
You're a man now, Idukwe.

47:00.675 --> 47:03.108
[speaking foreign language]

47:03.110 --> 47:05.110
[radio announcer]
<i>Ex-President F.W. de Klerk</i>

47:05.112 --> 47:07.746
<i>started off with
what Desmond Tutu later called</i>

47:07.748 --> 47:09.382
<i>a handsome apology.</i>

47:09.384 --> 47:12.684
[F.W. de Klerk]
<i>Apartheid was wrong.</i>

47:12.686 --> 47:14.787
<i>I apologize in my capacity</i>

47:14.789 --> 47:17.789
<i>as leader of the National Party</i>

47:17.791 --> 47:20.559
<i>to the millions
of South Africans</i>

47:20.561 --> 47:23.461
<i>who suffered
the wrenching disruption</i>

47:23.463 --> 47:24.530
<i>of forced removals</i>

47:24.532 --> 47:26.298
<i>in respect of their homes,</i>

47:26.300 --> 47:28.400
<i>businesses, and land,</i>

47:28.402 --> 47:30.302
<i>who over the years</i>

47:30.304 --> 47:32.537
<i>suffered the shame
of being arrested</i>

47:32.539 --> 47:33.671
<i>for pass law offenses.</i>

47:33.673 --> 47:35.574
[Linda] Hansie?

47:35.576 --> 47:37.175
What?

47:37.177 --> 47:39.478
[Linda] The fete,
Melissa's school fete.

47:39.480 --> 47:40.481
You should come.

47:42.250 --> 47:44.215
They'll wonder why
you aren't there.

47:44.217 --> 47:45.617
[de Klerk]
<i>...who for a long time were...</i>

47:45.619 --> 47:48.354
[Linda]
Sanette and Jan are coming.

47:48.356 --> 47:51.426
I told them we'd all go
for a <i>braai</i> with the kids.

47:52.659 --> 47:53.761
A <i>braai.</i>

47:55.496 --> 47:57.264
Yeah, let's go for a <i>braai.</i>

48:00.735 --> 48:02.834
[sighs] I'll say this
for those blacks,

48:02.836 --> 48:05.106
at least their leaders
stand by their men.

48:06.740 --> 48:09.508
[de Klerk] <i>...to the millions
of South Africans</i>

48:09.510 --> 48:12.411
<i>who suffered
the wrenching disruption</i>

48:12.413 --> 48:15.380
<i>of forced removals in respect
of their homes,</i>

48:15.382 --> 48:17.516
<i>businesses, and land,</i>

48:17.518 --> 48:19.217
<i>who over the years</i>

48:19.219 --> 48:21.353
<i>suffered the shame
of being arrested</i>

48:21.355 --> 48:24.255
<i>for pass law offenses.</i>

48:24.257 --> 48:27.626
<i>Who over the decades
and indeed centuries</i>

48:27.628 --> 48:29.662
<i>suffered the indignities
and humiliation</i>

48:29.664 --> 48:31.630
<i>of racial discrimination.</i>

48:31.632 --> 48:33.699
[radio announcer] <i>The head
of the ANC's legal department,</i>

48:33.701 --> 48:35.867
<i>Matthews Phosa,
remarked afterwards</i>

48:35.869 --> 48:37.802
<i>that de Klerk sat in Pretoria</i>

48:37.804 --> 48:40.106
<i>and knew everything
that went on</i>

48:40.108 --> 48:43.108
<i>in the ANC's Quattro camp
in faraway Angola,</i>

48:43.110 --> 48:45.047
<i>but nothing about Vlakplaas...</i>

49:18.713 --> 49:20.579
So, you're back, huh?

49:20.581 --> 49:22.084
Glutton for it, are we?

49:26.320 --> 49:28.789
So you have whipped that pig de Klerk.
So what?

49:30.925 --> 49:32.724
So,

49:32.726 --> 49:35.461
we are living
in Technicolor.

49:35.463 --> 49:38.597
Now they are saying
that it's time for

49:38.599 --> 49:40.599
the rainbow nation

49:40.601 --> 49:41.833
to unite.

49:41.835 --> 49:44.202
That's what they're saying,
is it?

49:44.204 --> 49:45.470
You, white boy in Hout Bay,

49:45.472 --> 49:47.472
with an up and under
behind the door?

49:47.474 --> 49:49.474
Terre Blanche and the AWB.

49:49.476 --> 49:51.376
You Green and Golds, is it?

49:51.378 --> 49:54.345
Shit, man,
that is buffalo dung.

49:54.347 --> 49:56.784
[Tutu] You know,
Mr. Blomfeld,

49:58.286 --> 50:01.954
when I left here last time,

50:01.956 --> 50:04.822
I didn't just even think,

50:04.824 --> 50:08.193
"Well...[laughs]...
that's that.

50:08.195 --> 50:09.396
It's over."

50:10.831 --> 50:12.463
I have fully,

50:12.465 --> 50:15.737
fully investigated
your case.

50:17.405 --> 50:18.406
And?

50:20.507 --> 50:21.710
And...

50:22.976 --> 50:25.913
amnesty for your crimes

50:28.349 --> 50:29.718
is highly unlikely.

50:31.652 --> 50:34.385
You showed your victims

50:34.387 --> 50:35.820
no mercy,

50:35.822 --> 50:39.825
and besides the...

50:39.827 --> 50:41.897
extreme brutality,

50:43.431 --> 50:45.697
your crimes reveal

50:45.699 --> 50:48.903
no political context.

50:53.507 --> 50:55.710
No political context?

50:57.677 --> 50:59.278
My context,

50:59.280 --> 51:00.912
as you call it,

51:00.914 --> 51:04.849
stretches back
some 300 years.

51:04.851 --> 51:07.385
When my ancestors
were farming this land

51:07.387 --> 51:10.021
and building its cities,

51:10.023 --> 51:12.391
yours were creeping out
of the bush,

51:12.393 --> 51:13.827
trying to murder them.

51:15.362 --> 51:16.829
That's context.

51:16.831 --> 51:20.501
My people were murdered
by yours.

51:21.568 --> 51:23.836
In Zimbabwe.
Yes, I know.

51:23.838 --> 51:25.871
Zimbabwe, South Africa?
Same difference.

51:25.873 --> 51:27.740
[Tutu] Is it?
Is it the same?

51:27.742 --> 51:29.541
I don't know.
You're the expert on context.

51:29.543 --> 51:30.711
You tell me.

51:34.782 --> 51:36.949
Your people

51:36.951 --> 51:39.617
[laughs]

51:39.619 --> 51:41.690
believed in this...

51:43.556 --> 51:45.659
this little
subversive book.

51:47.961 --> 51:50.662
It's a beautiful
little book.

51:50.664 --> 51:52.400
It's my favorite,

51:54.402 --> 51:57.068
which teaches us,

51:57.070 --> 51:59.771
"Proclaim liberty

51:59.773 --> 52:02.441
to the captive,

52:02.443 --> 52:05.747
sight to the blind

52:07.447 --> 52:12.786
and to set
the oppressed free."

52:13.920 --> 52:16.890
That's in Luke 4:18.

52:20.027 --> 52:23.028
Your people...

52:23.030 --> 52:25.930
felt they were being
oppressed

52:25.932 --> 52:27.335
by the British,

52:29.603 --> 52:31.769
they fought back

52:31.771 --> 52:33.574
and they became free.

52:35.608 --> 52:38.409
So you need to learn

52:38.411 --> 52:40.912
from your own history

52:40.914 --> 52:43.449
that when a people

52:43.451 --> 52:47.355
decide to be free,

52:48.655 --> 52:52.360
my dear friend,
nothing,

52:53.793 --> 52:57.929
absolutely nothing

52:57.931 --> 53:00.301
is gonna stop them
from becoming free.

53:02.503 --> 53:06.371
[clapping]

53:06.373 --> 53:08.639
Yes. Very good.

53:08.641 --> 53:11.443
Very high-minded of you.

53:11.445 --> 53:14.746
But there's something
you just don't get, <i>kaffir.</i>

53:14.748 --> 53:18.550
Something you just
do not get.

53:18.552 --> 53:21.854
Killing someone
is never political,

53:21.856 --> 53:24.923
no matter what
anyone says.

53:24.925 --> 53:28.028
Killing someone
is personal.

53:30.831 --> 53:33.867
It's always,
always personal.

53:36.670 --> 53:37.972
It's simple.

53:40.641 --> 53:42.974
You like to read, eh?

53:42.976 --> 53:45.778
Study on this,

53:45.780 --> 53:48.514
"Unconquerable will,

53:48.516 --> 53:50.416
study of revenge,

53:50.418 --> 53:52.950
immortal hate,

53:52.952 --> 53:55.653
courage to never submit
or yield,

53:55.655 --> 53:58.460
what else is not
to be overcome?

54:00.059 --> 54:02.059
Better to reign in Hell

54:02.061 --> 54:04.128
than to serve in Heaven."

54:04.130 --> 54:05.833
Lucifer.

54:08.034 --> 54:10.070
You quoted that poem
in your letter.

54:14.608 --> 54:16.809
So papa was a teacher,
so I'm assuming he knows

54:16.811 --> 54:19.381
it's "Paradise Lost."

54:21.181 --> 54:23.048
And if you don't,
you're just one more

54:23.050 --> 54:26.388
half-educated <i>mzee</i>
in my eyes.

54:29.690 --> 54:31.590
You're a dreamer, my old Hotnot.

54:31.592 --> 54:32.990
I grant you that.

54:32.992 --> 54:35.159
A fucking dreamer.

54:35.161 --> 54:36.528
Dreamer?

54:36.530 --> 54:37.565
Yes.

54:39.032 --> 54:42.834
I, for 40 years,

54:42.836 --> 54:45.970
I dreamed of voting...

54:45.972 --> 54:49.240
freely in a free country

54:49.242 --> 54:51.742
in the land of my birth.

54:51.744 --> 54:55.416
For 40 years,
I've been in the wilderness.

54:56.750 --> 55:00.688
Now, it's finally
come to pass.

55:05.559 --> 55:09.628
There was this one
neutralization

55:09.630 --> 55:11.762
and I was standing there
on this <i>stoep</i>

55:11.764 --> 55:15.566
covered in <i>kaffir</i> brain,
and blood, and shit.

55:15.568 --> 55:16.969
My old head was throbbing

55:16.971 --> 55:20.037
<i>like</i> babelaas...

55:20.039 --> 55:22.677
<i>and after the killings,
we set a fire.</i>

55:24.777 --> 55:26.945
And I could hear this voice
inside my head

55:26.947 --> 55:29.947
as clear as you're
hearing me now,

55:29.949 --> 55:33.050
telling me I had no dreams,

55:33.052 --> 55:36.688
no passion, no hope.

55:36.690 --> 55:41.526
"What is life without
them things?" it asked me.

55:41.528 --> 55:44.595
"I have passion, I have dreams."

55:44.597 --> 55:47.532
I remember shouting back.

55:47.534 --> 55:49.534
And all the boys were there,

55:49.536 --> 55:53.070
Francois, Hansie,
all the Hacksaw boys,

55:53.072 --> 55:54.673
<i>they were watching me
through the flames.</i>

55:54.675 --> 55:56.711
<i>The whole time that voice,</i>

55:58.012 --> 56:00.612
"What dreams, what dreams?"

56:00.614 --> 56:02.182
I had dreams!

56:05.085 --> 56:08.287
I had dreams once, I did.

56:08.289 --> 56:12.227
But you fucking people,
you stole them from me.

56:19.132 --> 56:23.101
How... How old...

56:23.103 --> 56:26.938
were you when you
joined the AWB?

56:26.940 --> 56:30.876
What the fuck is that
got to do with anything?

56:30.878 --> 56:34.045
How old?

56:34.047 --> 56:35.250
Seventeen.

56:37.117 --> 56:40.121
And what has it got
you, Mr. Blomfeld,

56:44.224 --> 56:47.992
33 years of hate?

56:47.994 --> 56:50.028
Fuck you.

56:50.030 --> 56:51.597
It's too much for you,
isn't it?

56:51.599 --> 56:52.930
The Commission?

56:52.932 --> 56:55.333
That's plain enough.

56:55.335 --> 56:57.970
I didn't come here
to discuss The Commission.

56:57.972 --> 57:01.238
You can't forgive
the likes of me.

57:01.240 --> 57:04.978
Breaking your faith,
isn't it, eh?

57:06.679 --> 57:09.880
I have watched the light
of life flicker out and die

57:09.882 --> 57:12.217
behind the eyes of so many
I have done.

57:12.219 --> 57:15.623
That is cock-stiffening,
I can tell you.

57:18.925 --> 57:22.663
I have ministered
to the dying,

57:23.998 --> 57:26.934
and I'm no stranger
to death.

57:28.369 --> 57:30.202
First,
when the knife goes in,

57:30.204 --> 57:31.970
they just don't believe it.

57:31.972 --> 57:33.575
They are in shock.

57:35.342 --> 57:37.175
Then is coming acceptance.

57:37.177 --> 57:39.744
Oh, yeah.

57:39.746 --> 57:43.048
They are grateful,
aren't they?

57:43.050 --> 57:45.751
Sometimes I feel
I can almost

57:45.753 --> 57:48.920
hear them whispering,

57:48.922 --> 57:52.257
"Thank you,

57:52.259 --> 57:53.728
thank you."

57:57.664 --> 58:00.264
So don't you come in here
and pontificate,

58:00.266 --> 58:03.367
you self-righteous doff.

58:03.369 --> 58:05.903
TRC has broken you inside,

58:05.905 --> 58:08.940
made the sham of your faith.

58:08.942 --> 58:11.208
I'm right, aren't I?

58:11.210 --> 58:13.045
You can't forgive the beasts

58:13.047 --> 58:16.748
that you confront every day.

58:16.750 --> 58:18.916
[laughs]

58:18.918 --> 58:20.918
That cancer
is eating you alive.

58:20.920 --> 58:22.820
You are so finished, boy.

58:22.822 --> 58:26.691
Don't you call me "boy"
again, Blomfeld.

58:26.693 --> 58:28.096
[Blomfeld] Or what?

58:41.407 --> 58:43.176
Under your mask...

58:47.246 --> 58:50.115
you're riddled

58:50.117 --> 58:51.919
with self-loathing.

59:05.465 --> 59:07.499
[sobs]

59:07.501 --> 59:10.104
Easier to...

59:13.106 --> 59:17.075
to be angry at the world

59:17.077 --> 59:19.447
than to be angry at yourself.

59:21.815 --> 59:23.150
I understand.

59:33.126 --> 59:35.894
When they arrested you,

59:35.896 --> 59:38.166
you had this on you.

59:42.503 --> 59:44.869
You hung onto it

59:44.871 --> 59:47.942
for 40 years.

59:49.342 --> 59:50.478
Why?

01:00:01.255 --> 01:00:02.423
Visit's over.

01:00:05.025 --> 01:00:06.193
What happened?

01:00:08.427 --> 01:00:10.394
And don't hide behind

01:00:10.396 --> 01:00:14.000
Aristotle, or Plato,
or Milton.

01:00:16.570 --> 01:00:18.068
You're right,

01:00:18.070 --> 01:00:20.938
you're right.

01:00:20.940 --> 01:00:24.108
I have to stare in the mirror

01:00:24.110 --> 01:00:28.014
at myself every day,

01:00:30.550 --> 01:00:33.453
and so do you.

01:00:37.190 --> 01:00:38.356
And you're not... you're not...

01:00:38.358 --> 01:00:41.559
you're not a fallen angel

01:00:41.561 --> 01:00:43.830
and I'm not God.

01:00:44.965 --> 01:00:48.469
We're both just men.

01:00:54.541 --> 01:00:55.943
One question...

01:00:58.978 --> 01:01:00.945
what do you know

01:01:00.947 --> 01:01:05.353
about this Operation Hacksaw?

01:01:13.860 --> 01:01:16.263
I said, visit's over, <i>kaffir.</i>

01:01:22.936 --> 01:01:25.103
You are locked inside

01:01:25.105 --> 01:01:27.340
two prisons, Blomfeld.

01:01:29.009 --> 01:01:32.209
One is made of concrete

01:01:32.211 --> 01:01:35.447
and barbed wire.

01:01:35.449 --> 01:01:38.617
The other one

01:01:38.619 --> 01:01:41.151
is worse

01:01:41.153 --> 01:01:44.358
because it's there
in your head.

01:01:47.594 --> 01:01:51.532
"The mind in its own place,

01:01:52.666 --> 01:01:55.233
and in itself,

01:01:55.235 --> 01:01:58.135
can make a heaven of hell,

01:01:58.137 --> 01:02:01.909
or a hell of heaven."

01:02:05.978 --> 01:02:07.380
That's Milton.

01:02:09.016 --> 01:02:11.449
So, if you're going
to read him,

01:02:11.451 --> 01:02:12.650
don't cherry-pick.

01:02:12.652 --> 01:02:16.990
You must read him properly.

01:02:32.572 --> 01:02:34.472
What the fuck is that?

01:02:34.474 --> 01:02:38.412
That is your way out
of prison.

01:02:40.179 --> 01:02:44.581
That could be a way out

01:02:44.583 --> 01:02:48.355
of your personal hell.

01:02:58.331 --> 01:03:00.067
[sighs]

01:03:04.036 --> 01:03:08.141
Come out, Blomfeld.

01:03:10.043 --> 01:03:11.345
Come out.

01:03:12.411 --> 01:03:14.214
Don't stay there.

01:03:16.682 --> 01:03:18.985
God is waiting for you.

01:03:20.753 --> 01:03:22.456
Come out.

01:03:48.081 --> 01:03:50.483
[Tutu] <i>He quoted Milton at me.</i>

01:03:53.152 --> 01:03:55.055
I lost my temper.

01:04:01.661 --> 01:04:07.264
But he knows about Hacksaw,

01:04:07.266 --> 01:04:09.601
and whatever Hacksaw is,

01:04:09.603 --> 01:04:13.507
it is linked to the death
of Mpho Morobe.

01:04:26.585 --> 01:04:29.153
[metal clanging]

01:04:29.155 --> 01:04:30.623
[Schmidt] Blomfeld.

01:04:37.496 --> 01:04:39.530
I'm thinking I go
get me a beer

01:04:39.532 --> 01:04:42.133
when the shift is done.

01:04:42.135 --> 01:04:46.107
Maybe a sweet piece
